title: For Sale/Trade:  SCAM ALERT!!!!!!
postcontent: I wanted to inform everyone about a scammer on here. He is copying listings already on Arms List and trying to pass it off as his own. The reason I know this is I purchased a gun 2 days ago and the same exact listing showed up again today. I contacted the seller to act as though I was interested in buying it. The reply I got was from a different email address. I then called the previous person I purchased the gun from and he had no clue about this new listing. The scammer would only except pay pal payment and would ship out the gun. He would not meet FTF even though he lived in the same city as I do. So I then looked "sellers other listings" and found he had listings in Michigan, Colorado, New Mexico and Florida. And all of the listings were items that were selling well below market value. Examples are a Sig AR15 for $1300, a S&W MP 40c for $300, and a AK47 for $600. So please look out for the following email and pay pal accounts. Email was jamesskinner271@yahoo.com and pay pal account is jcskinn@bellsouth.net . I can only assume his name is James Skinner. Don't trust this dude. There's no way you can privately sell so many guns in so many states. This is a fair warning to everyone.

title: For Sale/Trade:  MSAR STG 5.56mm Bullpup Rifle
location: Conway/Coastal Carolina, Myrtle Beach, South Carolina
postcontent:
I can't believe I'm putting this up for sale, but sometimes things for you to sell something you didn't think you ever would.  This is an immaculate MSAR (Microtech Small Arms Research) STG 5.56, serial # in the 8K range so it was after all the early problems were fixed, and it has the original Steyr AUG style 1.5x optic sight with the cross/circle reticle.  For those who don't know, this is an American made IMPROVEMENT on the original Steyr AUG rifle that was banned way back in the early 1990s and became instantly scarce and collectible; this rifle improved on feed and function, used modern polymers to make it even more resistant to damage and failures, and still has product support available in Pennsylvania!  This takes the plastic Steyr-type mags, and will actually accept surplus AUG mags which are actually pretty easy to find and no more expensive than decent AR mags.  I will include 3 mags with this gun, 1 ea 10rd, 30rd and 42 rd, and I have others available for additional cost if the buyer wants to deal.  

This rifle has been fired less than 50 rds and comes in the original factory box with all paperwork, gun lock, etc.  This is NOT a rifle you see every day, and I'll tell you what---not only is it cooler and wilder looking than even the most tricked out AR, but it's damn accurate, smooth as can be and is so short and compact with the bullpup design that accurate one-handed point fire out to 50 meters is a breeze!

I'm looking for $2200 cash, or possible trades for other "not so usual" quality firearms.  CDNN had one of these the other day for $3995, and most of the ones on Gunbroker are selling for $2000-$2500 with one 10 rd magazine and a flattop.  This one has the factory optic as well as the extra picatinny rail in case you want to mount another sight option.

title: For Sale:  Volunteer Enterprises Commando MKIII - Tommy Gun
location: Boulder, Louisville, Denver, Colorado, United States
postcontent:
For sale is my Volunteer Enterprises Commando MKIII .45ACP carbine, a semi-auto rifle styled after an Auto Ordinance Tommy Gun. This gun is a late model, manufactured in 1975, making it one of the highest-quality and most reliable Commandos out there. It uses 30-round M3 Grease Gun mags, which are still cheap and plentiful on GunBroker - much cheaper than actual Thompson 20-round stick mags. The receiver, 16-inch barrel, compensator, and magazine have been recently refinished in DuPont Teflon black at a cost of $250, and look excellent. It has been thoroughly cleaned and lubed, and only 5 rounds have been fired since the refinish to ensure proper function. 

I am also including a spare lower receiver, which I had planned to refinish and convert to use a genuine Thompson wooden handgrip and trigger, as well as the mechanism required to convert the stock to a push-button release, again emulating a genuine Thompson. The wooden buttstock can be easily removed with two screws, and the gun is quite fun to shoot without the stock. I am also including a spare ejector, ejector pin, and ejector spring, good spare parts to have around. It has the rock-solid feel and fun of a Thompson to shoot, at a significantly lower cost. 

33rd-edition of the Blue Book of Gun Values places the value of this rifle in good condition at $825, which does not include the spare parts. I am willing to accept offers in the neighborhood of $725. Full and partial trade offers will be considered, but I am most in need of the cash. As much as I don't want to admit it, it may not be possible to sell this gun (or mag) without a costly FFL transfer in Colorado soon, so this is a good opportunity to pick this gun up before that nonsense goes into effect. 

I am in need of funds quickly, so I would like to sell this today or tomorrow. For this reason, please call me on my cell phone at 720-987-4060 to arrange a meeting.

title: For Sale/Trade:  MSAR STG 5.56mm Bullpup Rifle
location: Conway/Coastal Carolina, Myrtle Beach, South Carolina
postcontent:
I can't believe I'm putting this up for sale, but sometimes things for you to sell something you didn't think you ever would.  This is an immaculate MSAR (Microtech Small Arms Research) STG 5.56, serial # in the 8K range so it was after all the early problems were fixed, and it has the original Steyr AUG style 1.5x optic sight with the cross/circle reticle.  For those who don't know, this is an American made IMPROVEMENT on the original Steyr AUG rifle that was banned way back in the early 1990s and became instantly scarce and collectible; this rifle improved on feed and function, used modern polymers to make it even more resistant to damage and failures, and still has product support available in Pennsylvania!  This takes the plastic Steyr-type mags, and will actually accept surplus AUG mags which are actually pretty easy to find and no more expensive than decent AR mags.  I will include 3 mags with this gun, 1 ea 10rd, 30rd and 42 rd, and I have others available for additional cost if the buyer wants to deal.  

This rifle has been fired less than 50 rds and comes in the original factory box with all paperwork, gun lock, etc.  This is NOT a rifle you see every day, and I'll tell you what---not only is it cooler and wilder looking than even the most tricked out AR, but it's damn accurate, smooth as can be and is so short and compact with the bullpup design that accurate one-handed point fire out to 50 meters is a breeze!

I'm looking for $2200 cash, or possible trades for other "not so usual" quality firearms.  CDNN had one of these the other day for $3995, and most of the ones on Gunbroker are selling for $2000-$2500 with one 10 rd magazine and a flattop.  This one has the factory optic as well as the extra picatinny rail in case you want to mount another sight option.

title: For Sale:  7.62x39 Russian AKM Saiga COMPLETE CONVERSION RARE!!
postcontent:
A Russian semiautomatic AKM rifle. This is a Saiga which has been COMPLETELY converted into an AKM type AK, unlike other lame conversions. This Russian AK can accept any mil spec magazine, accept a muzzle attachment without use of a crush washer, attach a bayonet, hold a cleaning kit and rod, have a pistol grip, and have a rear sight that is marked all the way.

Unlike cheaply made WASRS that have cheap American made barrels (which are cranked out to make a profit alone), Saigas have superrior cold hammer forged chrome lined barrels. Since Saigas are made in an actual AK factory and not built from worn out surplus parts, their quality can be trusted.

Rifle has had 300 rounds put through it with no malfunction.

Rifle comes with box, magazine pouch, 4 steel mil spec mags, 120 rounds WPA military classic, chrome lined muzzle brake, cleaning kit and rod, bayonet, sling. The rifle is wearing an Arsenal polymer stock set right now, which reduces weight, dissipates and resists heat better, and is more resistant to the elements. It has an Arsenal single stage trigger with a bolt hold open feature which can be removed if so desired.

UNIQUE FEATURES:

Riveted AKM trigger guard- Unlike other Saiga conversions, this one has a riveted trigger guard. Others simply bolt a bent piece of metal onto the receiver. This one had the old magazine latch removed, and a new magazine latch/ trigger guard riveted into place.

AK74 style rear trigger guard rivet- Most AK rifles in the U.S. lack this correct rear rivet. Arsenal rifles and stock Saiga rifles have these special rivets due to advances in trigger designs. Rifles without this rivet can accept some triggers, but not a true copy of a Russian trigger group (as sold by Arsenal). The addition of such a rivet guarantees a larger selection of trigger groups.

Mil spec handguard retainer- Other Saigas are being sold with cheesy bolt on handguard retainers. Little puny ones that hold on the barrel with loctite and some screws. Although they work, they are nowhere near as rugged as the original military version. This rifle has a standard Russian handguard retainer, and will accept any regular AK furniture without having to screw things on and off the barrel.

Front sight/ Gas block- This rifle has a gas block with an intact bayonet lug, and has an AKM front sight as well. This combo allows for the attachment of a bayonet and cleaning rod.

Threaded muzzle- Allows for attachment of muzzle brakes or flash hiders.

Bullet guide- Allows for use of regular AK magazines.

Trigger group- Arsenal single stage with bolt hold open feature

This rifle is in full compliance with 922r

title: For Sale/Trade:  MSAR STG 5.56mm Bullpup Rifle
postcontent:
I can't believe I'm putting this up for sale, but sometimes things for you to sell something you didn't think you ever would.  This is an immaculate MSAR (Microtech Small Arms Research) STG 5.56, serial # in the 8K range so it was after all the early problems were fixed, and it has the original Steyr AUG style 1.5x optic sight with the cross/circle reticle.  For those who don't know, this is an American made IMPROVEMENT on the original Steyr AUG rifle that was banned way back in the early 1990s and became instantly scarce and collectible; this rifle improved on feed and function, used modern polymers to make it even more resistant to damage and failures, and still has product support available in Pennsylvania!  This takes the plastic Steyr-type mags, and will actually accept surplus AUG mags which are actually pretty easy to find and no more expensive than decent AR mags.  I will include 3 mags with this gun, 1 ea 10rd, 30rd and 42 rd, and I have others available for additional cost if the buyer wants to deal.  

This rifle has been fired less than 50 rds and comes in the original factory box with all paperwork, gun lock, etc.  This is NOT a rifle you see every day, and I'll tell you what---not only is it cooler and wilder looking than even the most tricked out AR, but it's damn accurate, smooth as can be and is so short and compact with the bullpup design that accurate one-handed point fire out to 50 meters is a breeze!

I'm looking for $2200 cash, or possible trades for other "not so usual" quality firearms.  CDNN had one of these the other day for $3995, and most of the ones on Gunbroker are selling for $2000-$2500 with one 10 rd magazine and a flattop.  This one has the factory optic as well as the extra picatinny rail in case you want to mount another sight option.
